{"title":"6. METABOLISMO DE LOS ERITROCITOS","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología/6. METABOLISMO DE LOS ERITROCITOS-2025.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"METABOLISMO DE\\NLOS ERITROCITOS","guid":"HbFXbCYJBixAelupM4QZuQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"## 1. INTRODUCCIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"- Eritrocitos: células sin núcleo, mitocondrias ni organelos","guid":"HgKjdENnfgUm68clPi_4Dw","children":[]}]},{"id":"3","parent":"0","text":"- Características\\Nlimitantes:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"- Sin metabolismo oxidativo eficiente","guid":"Qpa2QlqmH215XDdXYp9cbg","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"3","text":"- Sin ribosomas para regenerar proteínas","guid":"XxvEti_bIVlrtLAUWTOEDw","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"0","text":"- Sin capacidad de\\Nsíntesis de lípidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"0","text":"- Sin capacidad de\\Ndividirse o adaptarse","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"0","text":"- Necesidades\\Nenergéticas para:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"0","text":"- Bombeo de iones contra\\Ngradientes electroquímicos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"0","text":"- Mantenimiento de\\Nla forma celular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"0","text":"- Mantener Fe de\\Nhemoglobina en estado\\Nreducido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"0","text":"- Preservar grupos sulfhidrilo de\\Nenzimas y hemoglobina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"0","text":"- Principal fuente de\\Nenergía: glucosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"0","text":"- Metabolizada\\Nprincipalmente por vía\\Nglicolítica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"0","text":"- Menor porcentaje por\\Nvía de las pentosas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"0","text":"## 2. METABOLISMO DE\\NLOS ERITROCITOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"0","text":"- Consumo de glucosa:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"0","text":"- ~20 g/día para 2 kg de\\Neritrocitos (adulto 70 kg)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"0","text":"- Representa 10% del\\Nmetabolismo corporal de glucosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"0","text":"- Ingresa por difusión facilitada\\N(GLUT-1, independiente de insulina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"0","text":"- Destino de la glucosa:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"0","text":"- 80-90%: vía\\Nglucolítica → lactato","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"0","text":"- 10-20%: vía de las\\Npentosas → NADPH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"0","text":"- Funciones del NADPH:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"0","text":"- Mantiene flexibilidad\\Nde membrana","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"0","text":"- Facilita\\Ntransporte\\Niónico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"0","text":"- Preserva Fe²⁺ en\\Nhemoglobina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"0","text":"- Previene\\Noxidación de\\Nproteínas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"0","text":"- Principales vías\\Nmetabólicas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"1. Glucólisis anaerobia (vía\\NEmbden-Meyerhof)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"0","text":"2. Metabolismo óxido-reductor\\N(vía pentosas y glutatión)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"0","text":"3. Metabolismo\\Nnucleotídico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"4. Sistema diaforásico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"0","text":"### 2.1.\\NGLUCÓLISIS\\NANAEROBIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"0","text":"- Proceso\\Nanaerobio de 2\\Netapas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"0","text":"1. Transformación de glucosa en G3P\\Ny DHAP (consumo 2 ATP)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"0","text":"2. Oxidación a\\Npiruvato/lactato (producción 4\\NATP)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"0","text":"- Balance neto: 2\\NATP/glucosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"0","text":"- Enzimas limitantes (catalizan\\Nreacciones irreversibles):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"0","text":"- Hexoquinasa (HK):\\Nglucosa → G6P","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"0","text":"- Fosfofructoquinasa\\N(PFK): F6P → F1,6DP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"0","text":"- Piruvatoquinasa (PK):\\NPEP → piruvato","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"0","text":"- Ciclo de\\NRapoport-Luebering:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"0","text":"- Derivación\\Nimportante de la\\Nglucólisis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"0","text":"- Transforma 1,\\N3-DPG en 2,3-DPG","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"0","text":"- 2,3-DPG: regulador\\Nde afinidad Hb-O₂","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"0","text":"- Se une a cadenas β de Hb\\Nfavoreciendo liberación de O₂","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"0","text":"- Desplaza curva de\\Ndisociación hacia la derecha","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"0","text":"- Elevación por: ↓pH,\\Nhormonas tiroideas, hormona\\Ncrecimiento, andrógenos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"0","text":"- Importancia de\\Ngliceraldehído-3-P-DH:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"0","text":"- Mantiene NADH en\\Nestado reducido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"0","text":"- Necesario para mantener\\NFe²⁺ en hemoglobina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"0","text":"### 2.2. METABOLISMO\\NÓXIDO-REDUCTOR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"0","text":"- Vía de las pentosas\\N(hexosa monofosfato):","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"0","text":"- Deriva 5-10% del\\Ncatabolismo de glucosa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"0","text":"- Funciona sin\\Nconsumo de oxígeno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"0","text":"- Puede aumentar 20-30 veces\\Nante oxidación intracelular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"0","text":"- Factor limitante:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"0","text":"- Cociente\\NNADP⁺/NADPH","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"0","text":"- Glucosa-6P-DH (requiere\\NNADP⁺, inhibida por NADPH)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"0","text":"- Sistema glutatión:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"0","text":"- Tripéptido sintetizado por 2\\Nenzimas que consumen ATP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"0","text":"- Forma reducida (GSH) protege\\Ncontra agresiones oxidantes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"0","text":"- Glutatión peroxidasa elimina\\Nexceso de peróxido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"0","text":"- Nivel de GSH mantenido por\\NNADPH y glutatión reductasa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"0","text":"- No difunde a través de\\Nmembranas eritrocitarias","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"0","text":"- Enzimas de\\Nsíntesis de glutatión:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"0","text":"- Delta-glutamilcisteinasintetasa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"0","text":"- Glutatión sintetasa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"0","text":"### 2.3. METABOLISMO\\NNUCLEOTÍDICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"0","text":"- Enzimas que contribuyen al\\Nmantenimiento del ATP:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"0","text":"- Adenilatoquinasa (AK):\\Nrecicla ADP a partir de ATP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"0","text":"- ATPasa:\\Ncontribuye al\\Nreciclaje","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"0","text":"- Adenosindeaminasa (ADA):\\Ntransforma adenosina en inosina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"0","text":"- Pirimidina-5-nucleotidasa:\\Ninterviene en degradación de RNA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"0","text":"- Relaciones\\Nmetabólicas:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"0","text":"- AK y ADA utilizan el mismo\\Nsustrato (adenosina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"0","text":"- Déficit de AK o exceso de ADA\\Ntienen expresión clínica similar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"0","text":"- Déficit de pirimidina-5-nucleotidasa →\\Nacumulación de nucleótidos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"0","text":"### 2.4. SISTEMA DE\\NDIAFORASAS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"0","text":"- Función: mantener Fe\\Nhemínico en estado reducido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"0","text":"- Sistemas diaforásicos:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"0","text":"- Principal: citocromo B5\\Nreductasa (activa)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"0","text":"- Utiliza NADH\\Ncomo sustrato","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"0","text":"- Transfiere electrones\\Nal citocromo B5","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"0","text":"- Citocromo B5 cede\\Nelectrones al Fe hemínico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"0","text":"- Secundario: usa NADPH\\N(normalmente inactivo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"0","text":"- Sin aceptor\\Nfisiológico de\\Nelectrones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"0","text":"- Puede activarse con aceptores no\\Nfisiológicos (azul de metileno)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"0","text":"- Útil en tratamiento de déficit\\Ndel sistema principal","guid":"","children":[]}]},"node_count":90,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Endocrinología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología","filename":"6. METABOLISMO DE LOS ERITROCITOS-2025","id":"map_519","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"6. METABOLISMO DE LOS ERITROCITOS-2025"}